Some days in the mountains are perfect—and this is a clip from one of those days🧡✨

Today, however, I woke up at 2:15am to hike a trail I’ve wanted to do for a while now.. but the weather had other plans and unexpectedly changed to rain/clouds. This just means when I finally get there, it’ll be even better😌

Follow for more ↝ @angelaliggs

node.text:
It took us over four hours to hike here. There was only one other woman on the trail who told us she saw four bears so we were a bit spooked. We made noise and looked around us the entire hike up. It was exhausting… but dang.. once we saw this campsite at the top all of that faded away☺️

Hope you have a chance to get outside today, wherever you are in the world♥️🌎

Photo shot by @juliiathompson

node.text:
Hazy days in the valley💚 Remember to be fire smart and not have campfires during the next couple months—especially during this extremely dry weather.

On average, 40% of wildfires in British Columbia are human-caused by activities like open burning, the use of engines/vehicles, dropping cigarettes, or anything else that creates sparks or a heat source. A campfire just isn’t worth it. 

I was camping last night and saw a fire on the other side of the lake. Don’t be those people🥺

Photo shot by @juliiathompson
